@startuml
title VHDX Dismount / Disappearance Failure Mode

skinparam shadowing false

actor "Windows/User" as Windows
participant "PowerShell Coordinator\nLLMStorage.psm1" as PS
participant "WSL Guard/Wrapper\nLLM.bash" as Bash
participant "Ollama Service" as Ollama
database "LLM VHDX Volume" as VHDX

Windows -> PS : dismount VHDX
PS -> Bash : request guard/cleanup

Bash -> VHDX : mountpoint check

alt volume still mounted
  Bash -> Bash : normal drain path
else volume missing
  Bash -> Ollama : sudo stop ollama
  Bash -> Ollama : sudo disable ollama
  Bash -> Bash : refuse new sessions
  Bash --> PS : failed closed
end

note over Bash,Ollama
When the authoritative LLM volume disappears,
the system does not attempt graceful session recovery.
It stops and disables Ollama.
end note

@enduml
